node.text: In the #SymmetryFlightDeck, fly with your fingertips — plane and #pilot become one like never before with the industry's first electronically linked sidesticks. Revolutionary leaps in safety, redundancy and reduced pilot workload are #TheArtOfExcellence.

node.text: #G700 — Experience the unparalleled interior of the industry's new flagship. Tap for a guided tour of the G700 with Gulfstream's director of design innovation. #ArtOfExcellence

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gulfstream Aerospace on September 08, 2021. May be an image of airplane, nature and sky.

node.text:
ICYMI, every international flight so far has been record-setting for the all-new #G700. After just claiming city-pair speed records en route to Doha and Paris, the aircraft set its third when it returned to Savannah (using #SAF from @JETEX #LeBourget).

7h 59m |  Avg. Mach 0.90 |  Surpassed previous record by 30 minutes

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gulfstream Aerospace on September 07, 2021. May be an image of airplane.

node.text: #OnThisDay in aviation history, the #G650 received FAA certification. The iconic aircraft family boasts 110+ speed records, the prestigious Robert J. Collier award and countless other achievements. This is the #ArtofExcellence.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gulfstream Aerospace on September 05, 2021. May be an image of airplane.

node.text: #OnThisDay in #aviation history, the #G280 received FAA certification. The super-midsize aircraft exhibits style and mastery in every flight. #ArtOfExcellence

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gulfstream Aerospace on September 03, 2021. May be an image of airplane and outdoors.

node.text: Get up close and personal with the #G500. #ArtOfExcellence.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Gulfstream Aerospace on September 01, 2021. May be an image of airplane.

node.text:
#NEWS: The all-new, fully outfitted #G700 set its first two city-pair speed records during its maiden international voyage — Savannah to Doha and Doha to Paris. Carbon offsets are being applied for both flights.

✈️ Savannah to Doha: 6,711 nm/12,428 km | Mach 0.88 | 13h 16m
✈️Doha to Paris: 2,953 nm/5,469 km | Mach 0.90 | 6h 15m

More details at the #linkinbio.
